Peru Stocks: Alturas, Casa Grande, La Pampilla, Minsur Decline

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-08-10T18:14:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/peru-stocks-alturas-casa-grande-la-pampilla-minsur-decline.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:42 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index fell 1.5 percent to 18,921.4. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index fell 0.8 percent to 2,433.55.  Mining and energy companies declined amid concern a
worsening sovereign debt crisis in  Europe  and slower than
expected U.S. growth will curtail demand for commodities.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, fell for the seventh time in eight sessions, shedding
6.3 percent to 3 soles.  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a
Canadian gold and copper exploration company, dropped 7.1
percent to 13 cents.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and
natural gas producer with operations in Peru, fell 2.9 percent
to $1.01. Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), Peru’s largest
petroleum refinery, declined 1.3 percent to 79 centimos.  Sugar producers weakened as prices for the sweetener fell
as much as 2.5 percent.  Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer,
fell 3.2 percent to 13.80 soles. Empresa Agroindustrial Pomalca
SA (POMALCC1 PE) slid the most in two months, decreasing 4.4
percent to 44 centimos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
